he electric blues and the worldwide spread of rock and roll. Working here in collaboration with writer and fellow musician Kim Field, he gets it all down. The Blues Dream of Billy Boy Arnold is a remarkably clear-eyed testament to more than eighty years of musical love and creation, from Arnold’s adolescent quest to locate the legendary Sonny Boy Williamson, the story of how he named Bo Diddley Bo Diddley, and the ups and downs of his seven-decade recording career. Arnold’s tale—candidly told with humor, insight, and grit—is one that no fan of modern American music can afford to miss.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBlues (Music)zIllinoiszChicagoxHistory and criticism. 0aBlues musicianszIllinoiszChicagovBiography. 0aHarmonica playerszIllinoiszChicagovBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / General.2bisacsh  aharmonica, chicago, southern, bo, diddley, muddy, waters, howlin, wolf, electric, sonny, boy, williamson, history, delta, guitar, music, research, hound, dog, taylor, atlantic, rhythm, songs, jazz, rock.1 aBoy Arnold, Billy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aField, Kim, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aField, Kim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107391900 cprintz978022680920540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226809342423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226809342/original  a978-3-11-073919-0  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles